      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHADOWFAX (1) found one better last time at Oakbank when favourite but still did a good job to grab second. Comes through stronger racing and keeps the 3kg claimer on to help under the big weight. Looks the one to beat. SUNDOGG (5) finished over a length away from SHADOWFAX last time but now meets him with a nice pull at the weights with the claimer engaged. Has proven tricky to catch but deserves strong consideration. MISS BOOM (3) got off the mark in great style two back but couldn't go on with the job last time. Drops back in trip and is drawn to advantage. Is sure to give backers a bold sight. WADAANA (6) hasn't won for a long time but has runs littered through her form that can measure up if presented on song. Keeping safe.",
